<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="_saving_the_mailbox_org_server_s_access_data_in_plentymarkets">2.3.2. Saving the mailbox.org server’s access data in plentymarkets</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>For plentymarkets to send emails such as order confirmations on your behalf, you need to save the <strong><a href="/en/crm/sending-emails#100">access data</a></strong> of the mailbox.org mailbox from which you want to send these emails in the <strong><a href="https://support.mailbox.org/knowledge-base/article/einrichtung-mit-sonstigen-mailprogrammen" target="_blank">Settings » Client (store) » Standard » Email » Access data</a></strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="46">2.3.3. Creating an additional email address (alias) for a mailbox</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Create an alias for the mailbox if you want the mailbox to be linked to more than one email address. The number of email addresses you can create per mailbox depends on the fee you select. Proceed as described below to create an additional email address for a mailbox.</p>
