<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="110">4.2. Activating menus</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The structure of the <strong>Menu</strong> tab corresponds to the menu structure in plentymarkets in order to facilitate finding the desired functions. Activate a menu to activate all of the submenus that it contains. If you want to activate individual submenus only, then you have to do so within the lowest level of this menu.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Assign every user of the <strong>Variable</strong> class only those rights required for his or her field of work. This way, security is increased and errors can be prevented in your plentymarkets system.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating the rights to menus:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open a user account.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Right</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Menu</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the menus that the user should have access to.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="115">4.3. Activating REST API rights</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>REST API</strong> tab, you specify which rights for the REST API are granted to a user of the <strong>Variable</strong> class. No REST API rights are activated by default. Users of the <strong>Admin</strong> class have all rights. Rights are granted separately for different modules and sub-modules of the REST API. Under <strong>Authorisation</strong>, for example, you define whether the REST API user can display rights or display, create and delete user roles.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating REST API areas:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open a user account.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Right</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>REST API</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate entire areas or expand areas to activate individual rights that the user should have access to.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Subsequently added, subordinated rights of a main module will be activated automatically for a user if the main module is activated. You can deactivate this function and manually activate new, subordinated rights.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Manually activate new, subordinated rights:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open a user account.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Right</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>REST API</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Activate new, subordinated rights manually</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="120">4.4. Activating SOAP API calls</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>SOAP API</strong> tab, decide which of the <strong><a href="/en/data-exchange/soap-api">SOAP API</a></strong> calls the user should be allowed to edit. No API rights are assigned by default. Not even for users who are assigned to the <strong>API</strong> class.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating SOAP API areas:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open a user account.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Right</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>SOAP API</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate entire areas or expand areas to activate individual calls that the user should have access to.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="130">4.5. Transferring rights</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>Transfer</strong> tab allows you to transfer an individual user’s rights to another user who belongs to the user class <strong>Variable</strong> or <strong>Admin</strong>. The settings that were saved in the Right tab will then be transferred to the selected user. You will see the users to whom rights can be transferred.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Transferring rights:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open a user account.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Right</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Transfer</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the areas that you want to transfer.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the users to whom you want to transfer.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Apply the selected rights to the selected users</strong>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="140">4.6. Activating rights for mobile access</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Mobile</strong> tab, you define which functions and key figures will be visible to users of the plentymarkets app.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating the rights for mobile access:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open a user account.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Right</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Mobile</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the functions and key figures that the user should have access to in the app.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="145">4.7. Unblock login</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Once an incorrect password has been entered several times in succession, the login will be blocked for the user for a certain time. The login can be unblocked by an administrator in the menu <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts » Open user</strong> by clicking on the button <strong>Unblock login</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="70">5. Creating roles</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Roles are used for grouping users and assigning the same rights to multiple user accounts without making changes to every single user account.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a new role:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Roles</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>New role</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>New role</strong> window will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a <strong>name</strong> for the role.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The role will open in a new tab and can be edited.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A role must be edited in order to define rights that are assigned to users with this role. Therefore, edit the role after creating it.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="80">6. Editing roles</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>After creating a role, it will open in a new tab for editing. The role is also added to the role overview so that you can open and edit it later. Roles are listed alphabetically in the overview. Every role is divided into 3 tabs. In the <strong>Settings</strong> tab, you can change the role’s name. In the <strong>User</strong> tab, you link users to this role. In the <strong>Rights</strong> tab, you assign rights to the role. The same settings used for users of the Variable class are also available for roles. For further information about rights, refer to the <a href="/en/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/manage-users#90"><strong>Assigning rights</strong></a> chapter.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Users of the Admin and Variable classes can create roles. Users of the Variable class must have the corresponding rights to do so.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking users to roles:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Roles</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open a role.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>User</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select users from the <strong>Available users</strong> column.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>single arrow pointed to the right</strong> to transfer the selected users to the <strong>Assigned users</strong> column.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Alternative: Drag and drop a user to the <strong>Assigned users</strong> column.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Assigning multiple users at the same time</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Press and hold <strong>Ctrl</strong> or <strong>cmd</strong>, then select multiple users by left clicking on them to assign them at the same time. The lower arrow buttons will transfer all users.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The role is assigned to the users in the <strong>Assigned users</strong> column. The <strong>roles</strong> in the <strong>Master data</strong> tab of a user’s account automatically match the settings made here. Assigned roles can be changed in both places of the system.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking roles to users:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open a user account.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select one, several or all of the roles in the <strong>Roles</strong> setting.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Linking user roles to users of the Admin class</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Administrators have all rights. However, it is important that roles are assigned to administrators for some processes. For example, administrators only receive role-specific emails when linked to the corresponding role.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph subhead">
<p>Example of use</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The administrator of the company MyStore creates multiple roles. All the rights to be assigned to every user are included in the Employee role. With this role, it is no longer necessary to assign these rights to every single user. Also, changes to rights concerning all users can be made in the Employee role. In addition to this role, the administrator creates the Warehouse technician and Accounting roles - specific roles for a small group of users only.</p>
</div>
