<div class="paragraph">
<p>Mr. Doe is a logistics specialist at MyStore and receives the Employee and Warehouse technician roles. If a user has several roles, the user’s rights are added up. Therefore, Mr. Doe receives the rights <strong>Clients (stores)</strong>, <strong>Webmail</strong> and <strong>Forum</strong> from the Employee role as well as the rights <strong>Warehouse</strong>, <strong>Stock</strong> and <strong>Fulfilment</strong> from the Warehouse technician role. However, he doesn’t have the <strong>Vacation</strong> and <strong>Accounting</strong> rights because the Accounting role wasn’t assigned to his user account.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_copying_roles">7. Copying roles</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you need an additional role which slightly differs from an existing role, copy the existing role and make changes in the <strong>Right</strong> tab of the copy.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Copying a role:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Roles</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a role.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Copy</strong> in the toolbar.<br>
→ The <strong>Copy role</strong> window will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> your settings.<br>
→ The role will be copied and open.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_sending_emails_to_all_users_of_a_role">8. Sending emails to all users of a role</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Roles allow you to send emails to all users of a specific role. For this purpose, an email address must be saved in the user’s account.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Sending an email to all users of a role:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Roles</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a role.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Send email</strong> in the toolbar.<br>
→ The email program will open. The email addresses of all users of this role are entered in the recipient field.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="60">9. Searching for users</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Filters help you to search for user accounts. Use the <strong>Class</strong> filter to display only users of a certain class, e.g. <strong>Variable</strong>. If no filters are used, all users will be displayed in the overview. The following elements and functions are available in the <strong>User</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
