</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="150">10. Linking roles and processes</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can also use roles for the <strong><a href="/en/basics/automation/processes/setting-up-processes">processes</a></strong> in the <strong><a href="/en/basics/automation/plentymarkets-client">plentymarkets Client</a></strong>. Create processes and link role-specific processes in the plentymarkets Client.</p>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/assets/EN-Managing-user-accounts.png" alt="EN Managing user accounts">
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><em>Image 1: creating a new process for a specific role</em></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking roles and processes:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Open the plentymarkets Client.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Processes » Processes per role</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>arrow</strong> in the line of a particular <strong>role</strong>. Then click on <strong>New process</strong> (image 1).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a <strong>name</strong> for the role.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the setting <strong>Role</strong> from the <strong>Visibility</strong> drop-down menu.<br>
→ The <strong>Role</strong> option will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a <strong>Role</strong> from the drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select whether you want users of this role to be able to <strong>change</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the <strong>warehouse</strong> for the process and a <strong>colour</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The processes are displayed for the selected role. Due to the visibility setting, the process will be available to users with the corresponding role only.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_creating_an_account_for_the_plentymarkets_forum">11. Creating an account for the plentymarkets forum</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The plentymarkets forum is a knowledge base that keeps on growing. It already contains many solved support queries. Our developers and other plentymarkets customers will help you solve technical queries you might have. In addition, you will find tips for working with plentymarkets and can exchange ideas with other plentymarkets customers. Proceed as described below to create an account for the plentymarkets forum. <strong>Admin</strong> class users can also create forum accounts for other users using this method.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating an account for the plentymarkets forum:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Open user</strong>.<br>
→ The user will open in a new tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>plentymarkets Forum</strong> area, click on <strong>Create account</strong><br>
→ The account will be created.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
